end: HighlightText component\n\n**New file: `frontend/src/components/HighlightText.tsx`**\n- Props: `text`, `query`, `className?`, `highlightClassName?`\n- Splits query into words, escapes regex specials, wraps matches in `<mark>` elements\n- Default highlight: `bg-yellow-200/60 dark:bg-yellow-800/40 rounded-sm px-0.5`\n- Returns plain `<span>` when no query — safe to use unconditionally\n\n### 4. Frontend: Enhanced search result cards\n\n**`frontend/src/domains/platform/checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx`**\n\nPass `searchQuery` and `searchMeta` to `CheckpointsList`. When in search mode, each card gains:\n\n1. **Highlighted commit message** — wrap title in `<HighlightText>` with the search query\n2. **Prompt subtitle** — show first session prompt (truncated ~120 chars) with highlighted terms, in `text-muted`. Only when prompt exists.\n3. **Match type badge** — next to checkpoint ID badge:\n   - \"Semantic + Keyword\" (blue) — matched both ways\n   - \"Semantic\" (purple) — conceptually related, no exact term match\n   - \"Keyword\" (green) — exact term match in indexed text\n4. **Matched files** — if query terms appear in `filesTouched`, show up to 3 matching filenames with highlights\n\nWhen not in search mode, rendering is identical to current (zero regression).\n\n## Card Layout (search mode)\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Implement [login] feature with OAuth                             │ ← highlighted\n│ \"Add [login] page with Google OAuth integration...\"              │ ← prompt\n│ a3b2c4d5e6f7 · Semantic + Keyword · 2h ago · @user · Claude     │\n│                                    +42 -8 · 3 files · 1 session │\n│ auth.ts, [login].tsx                                             │ ← matched files\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- **No prompt**: Prompt line omitted, card shows title + match type only\n- **Semantic-only match**: No terms highlighted (expected), \"Semantic\" badge explains why result appeared\n- **Long prompts**: Truncated to 120 chars + \"...\", CSS `truncate` as backup\n- **Special chars in query**: Regex specials escaped in HighlightText (e.g., \"file.ts\" works)\n- **`filesTouched` is null**: Matched files section omitted entirely\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | Return `RRFResult[]` from `searchCheckpoints()` |\n| `api/src/routes/cache.ts` | Build + include `searchMeta` in search response |\n| `frontend/.../checkpoints/api.ts` | Add `SearchMeta`, `SearchCheckpointsResponse`, `filesTouched` |\n| `frontend/.../checkpoints/hooks/useCommitsQuery.ts` | Update hook return type |\n| `frontend/src/components/HighlightText.tsx` | **New** — text highlighting component |\n| `frontend/.../checkpoints/pages/CheckpointsPage.tsx` | Wire search context, enhanced card rendering |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `npx tsc --noEmit` in `api/` — type check backend\n2. `npx tsc --noEmit` in `frontend/` — type check frontend\n3. `npx vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts` in `api/` — existing tests still pass\n4. Manual test: search for a known term, verify highlights appear, prompt shows, match badge renders\n5. Manual test: search for a semantic concept (no exact keywords), verify \"Semantic\" badge appears with no highlights\n6. Manual test: clear search, verify list returns to normal rendering\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/evisdrenova/.claude/projects/-Users-evisdrenova-code-entire-devenv-cli/1ce3dc88-a7e6-4707-a62c-39efdfab9804.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncommit and push this with title - initial frontend wip\n\n---\n\ncan we do somethign like this?\n\n\n\nthis is from v0 and it's a mix of the github search UI (which i attached a screenshot of) and what you came up with previously which was  just a little busy.\n\n---\n\